      "x": "HYPERVARIABLE LOOPS, ISOTYPES, AND LIGHT CHAINS. Within each variable region sit three regions of hypervariability (the CDRs) — three on the heavy chain, three on the light — and these six loops are the actual contact points for antigen. The heavy-chain constant region determines the isotype, and there are five options, after their Greek letters: μ, δ, γ, ε, α (giving IgM, IgD, IgG, IgE, IgA). The light chain constant"
