      "x": "LIVE SUB-TYPES. Attenuated: a disease-causing organism modified to be non-pathogenic that still multiplies. Reassortant: a combination of human and non-human viruses. Recombinant: insert gene(s) from a human pathogen into the genome of a non-pathogenic organism (e.g. baker’s yeast, baculovirus). All share the live-vaccine contraindication in the immunocompromised."
