      "t": "p",
      "x": "RECEPTOR EDITING. Covered in the B-cell negative-selection arm of LO 21.1, but worth isolating because it is high-yield and uniquely B-cell. In ~⅓ of immature B cells slated for apoptosis or anergy, RAG1/2 remain expressed and re-rearrange the light-chain DNA to generate a new BCR specificity — a last-ditch rescue. If the new BCR no longer binds self → the cell survives as a naive mature B cell; if it still binds self → it falls back to apoptosis or anergy. This is B-cell-only: T cells cannot edit their TCR."
