      "x": "THE HLA MECHANISM — THE KEY INTEGRATE. This is Step I of the model, explained at the molecular level, and it is the concept students most often get backwards. HLA-DRB is the most polymorphic class II locus, which is why so many disease-associated alleles map to class II. For T1D, the susceptibility allotypes are HLA-DQ2 (DQA1*0501:DQB1*0201) and HLA-DQ8 (DQA1*03:DQB1*0302); having both is additive (via a recombinant DQ). The mechanism: in a resistant person, HLA holds the self-peptide firmly, so a self-reactive TCR binds strongly in the thymus → apoptosis (the self-reactive cell is correctly deleted). In a susceptible person, the HLA lacks the contact residues to hold that peptide, so it \"flops\" — the self-reactive TCR, even with high intrinsic affinity, gets only a weak signal, and weak negative-selection signaling means survival. The"
