      "IFN-γ supercharges antigen presentation broadly. On responding cells it upregulates: MHC class I (so more infected cells are visible to CTLs), MHC class II on inducible cells (endothelium, some epithelium can now present to CD4), TAP-1/TAP-2 (more efficient endogenous loading), immunoproteasome subunits (LMP2, LMP7) (cleavage tailored to MHC I anchor preferences), and HLA-DM (better CLIP exchange in the MIIC). This is why Th1 responses fight intracellular pathogens — IFN-γ widens the visibility of infected cells and primes more cells to participate in antigen display. B — wrong because MAC, C9, perforin, granzyme are KILLING molecules — not antigen-presentation machinery. IFN-γ does activate CTL killing but doesn't upregulate these as part of presentation. C — wrong because FcγRI, CR1, TLR-4 are phagocyte and PRR molecules — separate function from presentation. D — wrong because surface IgM, IgD, Igα/Igβ are B-cell receptor components — not part of antigen presentation upregulation by IFN-γ. E — wrong because selectins, ICAM-1 are endothelial leukocyte-recruitment molecules — relevant to inflammation but not the antigen presentation machinery. [LO 7.2 — IFN-γ effects on presentation]",
