      "A clinical flow cytometry technician analyzes a bone marrow biopsy from a 4-year-old girl with newly diagnosed leukemia. The malignant cells stain positively for an intracellular enzyme normally restricted to developing pro-B / pre-B cells and pro-T thymocytes — the enzyme that adds random non-templated nucleotides at V(D)J coding joints during ontogeny. Which enzyme is this, and what diagnosis does its expression on the malignant cells support?",
